[In this outbreak, we only know that only a small number of cases have been demonstrated to be campylobacteriosis. The comment by Mod LL in Gastroenteritis - New Zealand: (Canterbury) waterborne 20120825.1261544 should be noted. "Sewage-contaminated water is likely to cause a variety of cases of gastroenteritis include viral and bacterial. Campylobacteriosis has been diagnosed in a small number of cases but other cases are likely to be present in other individuals."

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/2D26.]
